<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Seela Truelight</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I got Blessed Armor of the Risen at the zone in of Ssraeshza Temple from one of the giant cobras.<P>According to spdat, BAotR is 300hp, 30ac, 6 mana/tick, 144 minute duration self buff, and does not stack with PoTG or Focus. It does stack with Clarity2. For 6 mana/tick I'll give up 105hp extra from Focus, which is 405hp.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Mahtan Honorshield</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">That it doesn't stack with Focus I can understand, but why oh why can't it stack with PotG?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Troas Merwind</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I believe PotG has a minor mana regen component as well, so I'd guess that's why they don't stack.<P>------------------<BR>Troas Merwind<BR>Templar of Tunare<BR>Saryrn</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Twinskey Bab0linskey</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Yeah, PoTG has the same 6mana per tick, same as c1.  I sure hope it stacks with Aego.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">JanSorensen</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Gah<P>Not stacking with PoG is sad - but probably expected. Still nice though - just much less so. <P>Raid wise it will still be:<BR>Pog + Bulk + Marzin + Focus > Aego + AoR <BR>as thats 175 hp more though some ac less. <P>Much easier to be able to self buff though and great when you dont have a druid around.<P>Hmm, reading your post though it seems you base the stacking only on spdat info and not on an actual test. Might there still be hope or am I just grasping for straws....<P>------------------<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4264" TARGET=_blank>Mikar of the Nexus</A><BR>High Priest of Brell<BR><A HREF="http://companions.windsofstorm.net/" TARGET=_blank>The Companions</A><BR>The Tribunal</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Seela Truelight</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">The numbers come from spdat, but the only way to know if something stacks or not is to try it. BAotR stacks with Aegolism but not PotG.<P>Using PotG + BoF + Marzin + Focus is a total pain. With few exceptions, even for raids, to me it's worth the convenience to go with Aego + BAotR.<P>Today I got Judgement (750dd) in Ssraeshza Temple. Several spells for other classes also dropped. Cool place, nice graphics.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Arturo</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Is Ssraeshza Temple off connected to the Deep zone?<P>------------------<BR>Arturo Fuente<BR>60th High Priest of Mithaniel Marr<BR>Succoring Winds<BR>Bristlebane</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Seela Truelight</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">It is in The Grey, a vacuum zone you will need Enduring Breath to cross. Enter via the tunnel under the bluish pyramid structure not far from the Mons Letalis zone.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Arturo</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Yeah found it Friday.  Vary spiffy looking zone.  Was alone so was only able to test out the front mobs.  Do all the mobs on the first floor hit for 280?<P>------------------<BR>Arturo Fuente<BR>60th High Priest of Mithaniel Marr<BR>Succoring Winds<BR>Bristlebane</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Arturo</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Yeah found it Friday.  Vary spiffy looking zone.  Was alone so was only able to test out the front mobs.  Do all the mobs on the first floor hit for 280?<P>------------------<BR>Arturo Fuente<BR>60th High Priest of Mithaniel Marr<BR>Succoring Winds<BR>Bristlebane</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">daku inochi</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Two Armor of the Risen spell drops happened during our hunt of The Temple. I think we had about 14 spell drops all together.. maybe more. We cleared most of the first floor and cleared more than half of the second one, too.<P>Many of these mobs hit for mid to high 100's.  There were ALL blue and higher to me (60) and good experience, too.  The battles here remind me of the Lower Spider fights in Velkators.. same kinds of mob HPs and attack strengths.  The difference here is that the snakemen Warlocks will Gravity Flux as well as deal some serious AE ice damage. Resist Cold/Magic is mandatory in here. There are some healers but not nearly as many as Velks.  Their magical resistance is about normal, leaning towards above-normal. The deeper Shissars HT for upwards of 900+, so put a Rune on your puller.<P>The high level spells (54 to 58) were dropping about one in five mobs once you get a little deeper than the initial large room. There were ranged slot items which were VERY common drops - they had decent stats but nothing to drool over.  Other than the Shissar Fangs which dropped like rain  (Range slot item, all/all, Damage: 11  Delay: 15  Range: 170  Str: +5 Sta: +3 Agi: +5 Dex: +5 Poison Resist: +5) there were no other weapon/armor drops. <P>Our group was here with 16 people, ranging from 54 to 60.  We only suffered the occasional puller deaths and hunted for almost 3 hours.  Spawn times are fairly fast, so find a good spot and be ready for pops.<P>Daku Inochi<BR>60th High Priest, Quellious<p>[This message has been edited by daku inochi (edited 12-09-2001).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">JanSorensen</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">We just cleared first floor and 2nd floor up to the water spiral. Got 3 spells total. We had 13 people mostly level 60. Maybe they lowered the drop rate, but I also think they lowered MR as I could get mok to stick fairly consistantly after tash and malo.<P>------------------<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4264" TARGET=_blank>Mikar of the Nexus</A><BR>High Priest of Brell<BR><A HREF="http://companions.windsofstorm.net/" TARGET=_blank>The Companions</A><BR>The Tribunal</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Josiefuz</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Is this spell dropping anywhere outside the temple?  And what level group is needed to fight in the temple?  Could a single 55ish group do it?<P>-Fuz<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ladimor</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I was there with 2 groups in the Shissar Temple. All were 60s but me, 56 cleric. This zone is more suited to a small raiding party then a single group. The cobras look really neat. I felt like I was in a Indiana Jones movie going through an archeologic area. And it's true that the spawn rate is really fast.<P>I can't wait to get 58 so that I can buff myself. 6 mana regen per tick will be amazing. It's equivalent to C2. And that it can stack with C2/GoPT or mana song is great. Any clerics out there been fortunate enough to scribe and use this spell to confirm it's stacking ability? Has it dropped anywhere other than the Shissar Temple?<P>Ladimor Riganna<BR>High Elven Templar<BR>Bristlebane</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Splaktar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Armor of Risen is not equivalent to c2 heh, maybe c1, but certainly not c2...<P>------------------<BR>Splaktar/Gurgel/Samas</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Darianne</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"><BR>A thread out in the general forums, said C1 = 5 mana/tick and C2 = 11 mana/tick.  So, if this spell is equal to 6 mana/tick, it will be essentially Clarity 1... but I'm perfectly happy with that  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ladimor</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Oops. Correct. A little better than C1 at 6 mana regen per tick. But stacking with C2 (11 mana regen) or manasong will be ooh so nice.<P>Ladimor Riganna<BR>High Elven Templar<BR>Bristlebane</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
